{
  "stem": "11552.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when we had to bathe, we went into this little brook, my mother and I, and we went into it, we took our clothes and washed them, and put them on-- it was bitter cold-- and wrung them out.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You couldn't dry it, we put them on and they had to dry on our bodies.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "By the way, while I met him-- I want to tell you about something that happened.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "One Sunday, we were late to go and bathe.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Just think about what a beautiful-- [INTERPOSING VOICES]",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I found my mother in the summer of 1943, and now it was the fall of 1943.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so we-- we woke up late, and we went to this brook to bathe anyway.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And as I took off my clothes and I rinsed them out, because we didn't have any soap, put them on, and I had to put a rope around me to hold up that skirt, because I was a skeleton.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You could see all my cracked ribs.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I looked into the water, and I reflect my face.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And all I saw was big eyes, and the rest of us just really, like a skeleton.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I looked at my mother, and I asked her, Mommy, will I ever be a lady?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she said to me, Alicia, you are already a lady.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then she told me the definition-- [INAUDIBLE]'s definition of a lady is a person who is considerate of others.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Nothing to do with jewelry or beautiful clothes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then I put my little shirt on, and I said to myself, my mother said I was a lady.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
